Sentencas: We consider an LSCF (La1-xSrxCo1-yFeyO3-delta) cathode formed of straight fibers.
Titulo: Model of infiltrated La1-xSrxCo1-yFeyO3-δ cathodes for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Being LSCF a mixed ionic electronic conductor (MIEC), we consider that it features two separate charge conduction paths, one for electrons and one for oxygen-ions.
Titulo: Model of infiltrated La1-xSrxCo1-yFeyO3-δ cathodes for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Infiltrated dopant particles, adherent to the LSCF fibers, create contact points between the ionic and the electronic conductive paths, among which, otherwise, the charge transfer reaction would be negligible.
Titulo: Model of infiltrated La1-xSrxCo1-yFeyO3-δ cathodes for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Based on this picture of the doped LSCF electrode, a model is developed.
Titulo: Model of infiltrated La1-xSrxCo1-yFeyO3-δ cathodes for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The model includes the evaluation of (i) electron and oxygen-ion conduction along the LSCF fiber, and (ii) charge transfer reaction occurring at the doping particles and, possibly, at the electrode/electrolyte interface.
Titulo: Model of infiltrated La1-xSrxCo1-yFeyO3-δ cathodes for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The model is applied to infiltrated cathodes based on different LSCF scaffolds, and the results are compared to literature experimental data, demonstrating good agreement In particular, the model captures well the improvement of performance of the doped electrodes over the undoped ones, which can be five to tenfold or even more, and can bring the 1/R-p values to the order of magnitude of 10(5) S m(-2) at 1000 K. Deviations between model results and literature experimental data at high doping levels are discussed in terms of percolation and partial pore obstruction.
Titulo: Model of infiltrated La1-xSrxCo1-yFeyO3-δ cathodes for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells
